                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-none">

                      <i data-hook="cmps-review-star-rating" class="a-icon a-icon-star a-star-4 review-rating"><span class="a-icon-alt">4.0 out of 5 stars</span></i><span class="a-letter-space"></span><span data-hook="review-title" class="a-size-base review-title a-color-base review-title-content a-text-bold"> <span>Amazing value for money</span> </span>

                     </div><span data-hook="review-date" class="a-size-base a-color-secondary review-date">Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 11, 2023</span>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-mini review-data review-format-strip">

                      <a class="a-link-normal" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_rvw_avp?nodeId=G75XTB7MBMBTXP6W"><span data-hook="avp-badge-linkless" class="a-size-mini a-color-state a-text-bold">Verified Purchase</span></a>

                     </div>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-small review-data">

                      <span data-hook="review-body" class="a-size-base review-text">

                       <div data-a-expander-name="review_text_read_more" data-a-expander-collapsed-height="300" class="a-expander-collapsed-height a-row a-expander-container a-expander-partial-collapse-container" style="max-height: none; height: 300px;">

                        <div data-hook="review-collapsed" aria-expanded="false" class="a-expander-content reviewText review-text-content a-expander-partial-collapse-content" style="padding-bottom: 20px;"> <span>So, this little PC packs a punch. It's quiet, fast, and tiny. From a value for money perspective, it's amazing. Okay, it's not going to keep up with gaming PC's, but it's a fraction of the price, but for low end gaming, web surfing, watching YouTube etc, it's nigh on perfect.<br><br>There are, however, some caveats. Since these are basically using laptop components inside, connectivity is a concern. With only 3 USB-A ports, it limits options. Laptops have keyboards, trackpads, and webcams incorporated. Desktops don't. Connect a keyboard and a mouse, and you're left with one port. Add a webcam, and suddenly you're going to wonder how you can access your old flash drive. It might be worthy of consideration.<br><br>Then there is the bugbear of mine, that no mini-PC manufacturer seems to have addressed - the power switch. Wake-on Keyboard has been lost since PS/2 days, so turning a PC on now requires access to the PC itself. Stick it on the back of a monitor, under a desk, or anywhere not in plain sight, and it's a pain. It could easily be addressed - a simple connector on the case with an extension lead and momentary switch to put away from the machine to act as a second power switch, yet no-one seems to have considered it. Odd.<br><br>The BIOS is very limited - VERY. For those that like to tinker under the hood, this really isn't the machine for you. For example, I would love to be able to adjust when the fan kicks in, for example, as this, whilst quiet, is very regular (every 15 seconds for a 3 second blast, then off again) - and in a quiet room, this is noticeable. But no, there's no apparent relief from it. A nonsensical oversight, really.<br><br>My only other gripe is the power brick. The lead is relatively short, and as it is a wall wart rather than a separate brick and mains lead, there is no simple way to extend it.<br><br>Overall, it's highly recommended, if you accept the caveats. The presentation of the machine is amazing, and everything you could want is included in the box, including a HDMI cable and VESA mounting bracket, even the screws to attach the bracket to the monitor. For the price, it's outstanding.</span> 

                        </div>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-none">

                      <i data-hook="cmps-review-star-rating" class="a-icon a-icon-star a-star-5 review-rating"><span class="a-icon-alt">5.0 out of 5 stars</span></i><span class="a-letter-space"></span><span data-hook="review-title" class="a-size-base review-title a-color-base review-title-content a-text-bold"> <span>Great little machine</span> </span>

                     </div><span data-hook="review-date" class="a-size-base a-color-secondary review-date">Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 6, 2023</span>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-mini review-data review-format-strip">

                      <a class="a-link-normal" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_rvw_avp?nodeId=G75XTB7MBMBTXP6W"><span data-hook="avp-badge-linkless" class="a-size-mini a-color-state a-text-bold">Verified Purchase</span></a>

                     </div>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-small review-data">

                      <span data-hook="review-body" class="a-size-base review-text">

                       <div data-a-expander-name="review_text_read_more" data-a-expander-collapsed-height="300" class="a-expander-collapsed-height a-row a-expander-container a-expander-partial-collapse-container" style="max-height: none; height: 300px;">

                        <div data-hook="review-collapsed" aria-expanded="false" class="a-expander-content reviewText review-text-content a-expander-partial-collapse-content" style="padding-bottom: 20px;"> <span>I'm a newbie when it comes to the new mini PC's. Compared to my old desktop, which I've had for at least 10 years, it looks like a mouse against goliath. That said, when you look at its specs it's clearly a serious piece of equipment. It comes with Windows 11 pro pre-installed. Obviously I was quite nervous about a machine this small performing as well as described, but I needn't have worried. Once I had connected everything to it's numerous ports and to my 5g wifi network it was a breeze to sign into Windows and configure from there. A week later and all is not only well, but is performing way better than my old, much larger machine, which was clearly wearing out. I've also managed to expand the RAM memory to 16gb (double the installed). Contrary to what the sales pitch says the installed memory should only be doubled, as this is the recommendation for the Intel Celeron processor installed. You won't get any better performance by expanding to 32gb, and there are only 2 RAM slots in the machine anyway. The internal memory can also be expanded up to 1tb if needed. Everything on screen works super fast with no lag. Also the machine is extremely quiet. I've not heard a murmor from it and it's on 24/7. I also have my emby server on it, with all my media on an external HD, and the server works perfectly well. I'm trying hard to find any fault with it to be honest. For everyday use this is perfect for my needs. However if you are a serious gamer you would probably need a machine with higher specs. Overall I'm extremely pleased I made the investment. At the price especially, this is a bargain piece of quality equipment. It's solidly made, and looks attractive too. It's also portable of course because of its size. A big thumbs up from me.</span> 

                        </div>

                     </div><span data-hook="review-date" class="a-size-base a-color-secondary review-date">Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 2, 2023</span>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-mini review-data review-format-strip">

                      <a class="a-link-normal" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_rvw_avp?nodeId=G75XTB7MBMBTXP6W"><span data-hook="avp-badge-linkless" class="a-size-mini a-color-state a-text-bold">Verified Purchase</span></a>

                     <div class="a-row a-spacing-small review-data">

                      <span data-hook="review-body" class="a-size-base review-text">

                       <div data-a-expander-name="review_text_read_more" data-a-expander-collapsed-height="300" class="a-expander-collapsed-height a-row a-expander-container a-expander-partial-collapse-container" style="max-height: none; height: 300px;">

                        <div data-hook="review-collapsed" aria-expanded="false" class="a-expander-content reviewText review-text-content a-expander-partial-collapse-content" style="padding-bottom: 20px;"> <span>My traditional bulky office computer with windows 10 was slow to boot up compared with my Huawei Laptop. And while Microsoft eventually decided that the laptop could be upgraded to windows 11 (and the upgrade was quick and uneventful) , my traditional office machine could not be upgraded. Initially I seemed to have two options - a reconditioned office machine with Windows 11 or a new office machine costing 500 or more. But then I found that a number of compact machines were available at around 200+ I decided on the Geekcom which was on special offer and cannot praise it enough. All my browser information and passwords quickly transferred and it is amazingly fast when coping with all my office needs (I am not into gaming) Such an improvement over past windows upgrades<br>However, I am adding a footnote. While my Brother Printer immediately made the transition from Windows 10 to Windows 11, my Epson scanner did not. It is a V300 and Epson have not upgraded the driver. It is said that Windows 11 will provide a generic scanner programme under such circumstances, but after several hours I cannot get it to recognise my scanner. I will update this if and when I find a solution<br>Further footnote. I have now found an Epson driver for my scanner which does work. Previously the scanned documents would automatically be added to the list of such documents, but now I now have to indicate where I want them sent. I have also received good support from Geekom and it seems that the software for identifing old scanners and using the generic programme in Windows 11 may have been been improved.</span>

        new Image().src = jsCssAssets[i];

      }

    }

    else if (isFireFox) {

      for (var i=0; i<jsCssAssets.length; i++) {

        var o =  document.createElement("object");

        o.data = jsCssAssets[i];

        o.width = o.height = 0;

        document.body.appendChild(o);

      }

    }

}

        setTimeout(prefetchTYPAssets, 2000);

    };

    if (window.addEventListener) {

        window.addEventListener("load", onload);

    } else if (window.attachEvent) { /* for <= IE 8 */

        window.attachEvent("onload", onload);

    }

     <script type="text/javascript">(function ($Nav) {

"use strict";



if (typeof $Nav === 'undefined' || $Nav === null || typeof $Nav.when !== 'function') {

    return;

}



$Nav.when('$', 'data', 'flyout.yourAccount', 'sidepanel.csYourAccount',

          'config')

    .run("BuyitAgain-YourAccount-SidePanel",

    function ($, data, yaFlyout, csYourAccount, config) {

        if (config.disableBuyItAgain) {

            return;

        }

        var render = function (data) {

            if (data.dramResult) {

                var widgetHtml = data.dramResult;

                navbar.sidePanel({

                    flyoutName: 'yourAccount',

                    data: {html: widgetHtml}

                });

            }

        };



        var renderBuyItAgain = function (biaData) {

            if (csYourAccount) {

                csYourAccount.register(render, biaData);

            } else {

                render(biaData);

            }

        };



        var truncateAndRestructureYaFlyout = function() {

            if (window.P) {

                P.when('A', 'a-truncate').execute(function(A, truncate) {

                    var truncateElements = A.$('.a-truncate');

                    A.each(truncateElements, function(element) {

                        truncate.get(element).update();

                    });

                    var recommendationsWidget = document.getElementById('bia-hcb-widget');

                    if (recommendationsWidget) { 

                        var navFlyout = recommendationsWidget.parentElement;

                        var navFlyoutPaddingBottom = parseInt(window.getComputedStyle(navFlyout).getPropertyValue('padding-bottom'));

                        var navFlyoutContentHeight = navFlyout.clientHeight - navFlyoutPaddingBottom;

                        while (recommendationsWidget.offsetHeight > navFlyoutContentHeight && recommendationsWidget.offsetHeight > 0){

                            var recommendations = recommendationsWidget.querySelectorAll('.biaNavFlyoutFaceout');

                            if (recommendations.length <= 1) {

                                break;

                            }

                            var lastRecommendation = recommendations[recommendations.length - 1];

                            lastRecommendation.parentElement.removeChild(lastRecommendation);

                        }

                    }

               });

            }

        };



        yaFlyout.sidePanel.onData(truncateAndRestructureYaFlyout);

        yaFlyout.onShow(truncateAndRestructureYaFlyout);



    yaFlyout.onRender(function() {

            $.ajax({

                url: '/gp/bia/external/bia-hcb-ajax-handler.html',

                data: {"biaHcbRid":"ZSCMWV81JWP0H8MWCK8M"},

                dataType: 'json',

                timeout: 4*1000,

                success: renderBuyItAgain,

                error: function (jqXHR, textStatus, errorThrown) {

                }

            });

        });

    });

})(window.$Nav);</script>
